                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.H Continental Solidarity/94: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-12-21T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 21, 1938—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. My 84, December 21, 3 p.m. The President requested me to read the text of the
                    declaration in Cabinet meeting this afternoon and he expressed his entire
                    approval of the formula proposed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
